  "local_port": 43022,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I completely delete all Adobe CS6 files on my Mac?",
  "response": "To completely delete all Adobe CS6 files on your Mac, follow these steps carefully. This process will help you remove the applications, associated files, and preferences. Please note that this is a thorough process and should be done carefully.\n\n### Step 1: Uninstall Adobe CS6 Applications\n\n1. **Open Finder** and navigate to the **Applications** folder.\n2. **Locate the Adobe CS6 applications** you want to uninstall. These might include Adobe Photoshop CS6, Adobe Illustrator CS6, Adobe InDesign CS6, etc.\n3. **Drag each application to the Trash** or right-click and select **Move to Trash**.\n\n### Step 2: Remove Adobe CS6 Preferences and Support Files\n\n1. **Open the Terminal** application. You can find it in **Applications > Utilities > Terminal**.\n2. Run the following commands to delete Adobe CS6 preferences and support files:\n\n```bash\n# Remove Adobe CS6 preferences\nrm -rf ~/Library/Preferences/Adobe\\ CS6*\n\n# Remove Adobe CS6 application support files\nrm -rf ~/Library/Application\\ Support/Adobe\\ CS6*\n\n# Remove saved application states\nrm -rf ~/Library/Saved\\ Application\\ State/com.adobe.*\n\n# Remove Adobe CS6 cache files\nrm -rf ~/Library/Caches/Adobe\\ CS6*\n```\n\n### Step 3: Remove Adobe CS6 Logs and Crash Reporter Data\n\n1. Continue in the **Terminal** and run the following commands:\n\n```bash\n# Remove Adobe CS6 logs\nrm -rf ~/Library/Logs/Adobe\\ CS6*\n\n# Remove Adobe CS6 crash reporter data\nrm -rf ~/Library/CrashReporter/Adobe\\ CS6*\n```\n\n### Step 4: Remove Adobe CS6 Installation Files\n\n1. Navigate to the folder where you originally installed Adobe CS6. Typically, this is in the **Applications/Utilities/Adobe Installers** folder.\n2. **Delete any remaining Adobe CS6 installer files** by dragging them to the **Trash** or right-clicking and selecting **Move to Trash**.\n\n### Step 5: Empty the Trash\n\n1. Right-click on the **Trash** icon in the dock and select **Empty Trash**.\n2. Confirm that you want to permanently delete the items.\n\n### Step 6: Restart Your Mac\n\n1. **Restart your Mac** to ensure all processes related to Adobe CS6 are terminated and all files are removed.\n\n### Additional Steps (Optional)\n\nIf you want to be absolutely sure that all Adobe CS6 files are removed, you can use a third-party uninstaller application like AppCleaner or CleanMyMac. These tools can help identify and remove any remaining files that might have been missed.\n\n### Final Check\n\nAfter following these steps, you can use the **Terminal** to check if any Adobe CS6 files remain:\n\n```bash\n# Search for remaining Adobe CS6 files\nmdfind -name Adobe\\ CS6\n```\n\nIf any files are found, you can manually delete them or use the third-party uninstaller mentioned above.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to completely delete all Adobe CS6 files from your Mac.",
